The paper discusses a game-theoretic model for incentivizing information-sharing in research, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The use of online collaborative-research platforms and the study of strategic behavior of agents also suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of preventing duplication of work and ensuring progress in research, which could be relevant to the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
